The article discusses the National Day of Making, which celebrates the tradition of innovation in the United States. It highlights the accessibility of technology and tools, such as 3D printers and design software, that allow people to create and invent. The government is supporting this movement by providing resources and opportunities for young people to get involved in making. The article also mentions the White House Maker Faire, an event that showcases makers from various fields. The President calls on Americans to encourage creativity and invention in their communities, and proclaims June 18, 2014, as National Day of Making.